Durban - An elderly woman had to be airlifted to hospital after she was critically injured after being knocked by a car in Village Road in Kloof, west of Durban on Thursday afternoon. 

According to Rescue Care's Garrith Jamieson, when emergency rescue teams arrived at the scene, they assessed the woman and found that she had sustained critical injuries. 














